Vagrant Setup
=========

You can use Vagrant for setting up a virtual Linux development environment under Windows.
For this, you need to

1. Install Vagrant from http://downloads.vagrantup.com/
2. Install VirtualBox from https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads
3. Run vagrant up
4. Once the provisioning script has run through, you can run vagrant ssh
5. cd /home/fuzztrees
6. fab -l

Edit the Vagrantfile in order to get graphical mode: uncomment
#config.vm.boot_mode = :gui